  "text": "## Findings\n\nThis inventory documents references to deprecated Kafka producer configuration keys across the evaluated repositories:\n\n### Deprecated Configuration Keys\n1. **block.on.buffer.full** - Deprecated since Kafka 0.9.0.0, removed in later versions\n2. **metadata.fetch.timeout.ms** - Deprecated since Kafka 0.9.0.0, removed in later versions\n3. **timeout.ms** - The old producer timeout configuration, deprecated in favor of delivery.timeout.ms\n\n### Repository Analysis\n\n#### Apache Kafka (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489)\nThe target Kafka repository does NOT contain active code references to these deprecated configuration keys. The configuration constants and usage were removed from ProducerConfig.java and related files. However, the deprecation/removal history is documented in docs/upgrade.html, confirming these keys were deprecated in Kafka 0.9.0.0 and removed from the codebase.\n\n#### Apache Flink (github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc)  \nNo references to the deprecated Kafka producer configuration keys were found in the Flink repository.\n\n#### Apache Camel (github.com/sg-evals/camel--1006f047)\nThe Camel repository contains references to the deprecated configuration `block.on.buffer.full` in Kafka-related documentation and generated code:\n\n**Source Files:**\n1. **components/camel-kafka/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/kafka/KafkaConfiguration.java** (line 1549)\n   - Contains documentation/javadoc referencing: \"on the preference specified by block.on.buffer.full\"\n\n2. **dsl/camel-endpointdsl/src/generated/java/org/apache/camel/builder/endpoint/dsl/KafkaEndpointBuilderFactory.java** (lines 2640, 2663)\n   - Generated DSL code containing: \"block.on.buffer.full\" in method documentation\n\n3. **dsl/camel-componentdsl/src/generated/java/org/apache/camel/builder/component/dsl/KafkaComponentBuilderFactory.java** (line 1108)\n   - Generated component DSL code referencing: \"block.on.buffer.full\"\n\n**Configuration/Documentation Files:**\n4. **catalog/camel-catalog/src/generated/resources/org/apache/camel/catalog/components/kafka.json**\n   - Generated metadata for the Kafka component\n\n5. **components/camel-kafka/src/generated/resources/META-INF/org/apache/camel/component/kafka/kafka.json**\n   - Generated component configuration schema\n\n### Summary\nThe deprecated Kafka producer configuration keys (`block.on.buffer.full`, `metadata.fetch.timeout.ms`, `timeout.ms`) have been removed from the main Kafka codebase (as of version 3.8.0+). References to `block.on.buffer.full` remain in the Apache Camel project's documentation strings and generated code, likely because these are auto-generated from Kafka client documentation that includes legacy configuration descriptions for informational purposes."
