  "text": "## Findings\n\nThis inventory documents references to deprecated Kafka producer configuration keys across the evaluated repositories.\n\n### Deprecated Configuration Keys\n1. **block.on.buffer.full** - Deprecated since Kafka 0.9.0.0, removed in later versions. Controlled producer behavior when the buffer was full (throw exception or block).\n2. **metadata.fetch.timeout.ms** - Deprecated since Kafka 0.9.0.0, removed in later versions. Configured the timeout for metadata fetch requests.\n3. **timeout.ms** - The old producer timeout configuration, deprecated in favor of delivery.timeout.ms. Replaced by delivery.timeout.ms for controlling maximum time messages can be in flight.\n\n### Repository Analysis\n\n#### Apache Kafka (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489)\nThe target Kafka repository does NOT contain active code references to these deprecated configuration keys in source files. The configuration constants and usage were removed from ProducerConfig.java and related files during previous Kafka versions. The deprecation/removal history is documented in docs/upgrade.html, confirming these keys were deprecated in Kafka 0.9.0.0 and removed from the codebase.\n\n#### Apache Flink (github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc)  \nNo references to the deprecated Kafka producer configuration keys were found in the Flink repository.\n\n#### Apache Camel (github.com/sg-evals/camel--1006f047)\nThe Camel repository contains references to the deprecated configuration `block.on.buffer.full` in Kafka-related documentation and generated code:\n\n**Source Files with References:**\n1. **components/camel-kafka/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/kafka/KafkaConfiguration.java**\n   - Line 1549: Javadoc comment for `setBufferMemorySize()` method references \"block.on.buffer.full\"\n   - Context: Documentation explaining the bufferMemorySize configuration property mentions the deprecated config key\n\n2. **dsl/camel-endpointdsl/src/generated/java/org/apache/camel/builder/endpoint/dsl/KafkaEndpointBuilderFactory.java**\n   - Lines 2640, 2663: Generated DSL code documentation for bufferMemorySize configuration\n   - Context: Auto-generated JavaDoc for the endpoint builder factory\n\n3. **dsl/camel-componentdsl/src/generated/java/org/apache/camel/builder/component/dsl/KafkaComponentBuilderFactory.java**\n   - Line 1108: Generated component DSL documentation for bufferMemorySize configuration\n   - Context: Auto-generated JavaDoc for the component builder factory\n\n**Configuration/Metadata Files:**\n4. **catalog/camel-catalog/src/generated/resources/org/apache/camel/catalog/components/kafka.json**\n   - Generated metadata catalog for the Kafka component (JSON format)\n\n5. **components/camel-kafka/src/generated/resources/META-INF/org/apache/camel/component/kafka/kafka.json**\n   - Generated component configuration schema (JSON format)\n\n### Summary\nThe deprecated Kafka producer configuration keys (`block.on.buffer.full`, `metadata.fetch.timeout.ms`, `timeout.ms`) have been removed from the main Kafka codebase (as of version 3.8.0+). References to `block.on.buffer.full` remain in the Apache Camel project's documentation strings and generated code, specifically in the documentation for the `bufferMemorySize` configuration option. These references are preserved in auto-generated code and documentation that was sourced from Kafka client documentation including legacy configuration descriptions for informational purposes.\n\n**Key Finding:** Only the `block.on.buffer.full` deprecated key appears in references across the three evaluated repositories. No references to `metadata.fetch.timeout.ms` or the old `timeout.ms` were found in the evaluated codebases."
